This paper deals with the study of codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves the partitioning of codes into classes, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper introduces a partial order in the set of submonoids of a monoid, which is a topic in formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL) and also involves the study of algebraic structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the characteristic property of a monoid generated by a maximal UD code, which is a topic in logic and computation (cs.LO).
